WEBVTT

00:05.339 --> 00:07.466
Jesus, you mind?

00:09.010 --> 00:11.679
Oh, shit, man,
what is your problem?

00:14.682 --> 00:16.183
All right.
Would you just back up

00:16.267 --> 00:18.811
a little bit?
Thank you.

00:18.894 --> 00:21.063
You're both going
to nursery school,

00:21.147 --> 00:22.940
but you can't ever be in
the same room at the same time,

00:23.024 --> 00:24.358
and you're both named Amy now.

00:24.442 --> 00:25.609
Are you fucking my sister?

00:25.693 --> 00:27.278
Debbie and I are friends.

00:27.361 --> 00:29.864
Carl thinks if two women
are friends, they must be gay.

00:29.947 --> 00:31.240
<i>No, I think Debbie's
gay because she follows you</i>

00:31.323 --> 00:32.700
<i>around like
a little puppy dog.</i>

00:32.783 --> 00:33.909
<i>I'm not getting
total gay vibes,</i>

00:33.993 --> 00:35.119
but it's inconclusive,

00:35.202 --> 00:36.829
so...I'd say yeah,

00:36.912 --> 00:39.206
she'll probably eventually
end up gay.

00:39.290 --> 00:40.499
I think we should break up.

00:40.583 --> 00:41.542
Why, 'cause you love
my sister?

00:41.625 --> 00:43.002
No, because you're too clingy.

00:43.085 --> 00:44.253
Call me

00:44.336 --> 00:45.504
when you're not so needy.

00:45.588 --> 00:46.589
I'm pregnant.

00:46.672 --> 00:47.631
Are you sure it's mine?

00:47.715 --> 00:49.550
Yeah, I'm sure it's yours.

00:49.633 --> 00:50.926
The last thing I need
in my life

00:51.010 --> 00:52.219
is a man telling me
what to do.

00:52.303 --> 00:54.221
I really don't give a shit
about what you think,

00:54.305 --> 00:55.639
but I do understand

00:55.723 --> 00:57.516
that you might have
some feelings about this.

00:57.600 --> 00:59.894
If you decide to have
this baby,

00:59.977 --> 01:01.687
I want to make damn sure
it has a father.

01:01.771 --> 01:03.230
I own this house!

01:03.314 --> 01:04.940
The title is in my name!

01:05.024 --> 01:06.609
I'm not letting you live here,

01:06.692 --> 01:08.235
not with Liam
and not with Franny.

01:08.319 --> 01:09.570
Fuck you!

01:09.653 --> 01:10.905
Lip kicked you
out of the house?

01:10.988 --> 01:12.323
Yeah, you believe
that motherfucker?

01:12.406 --> 01:13.908
I'm carrying my shit around
in garbage bags.

01:13.991 --> 01:14.992
You're a bad drunk.

01:15.076 --> 01:16.660
When you drink, you get mean.

01:16.744 --> 01:18.454
A good drunk is fun.

01:18.537 --> 01:20.998
<i>A bad drunk
wants to have a fight.</i>

01:21.082 --> 01:22.208
<i>If you really love her,</i>

01:22.291 --> 01:24.126
and you really are her friend,

01:24.210 --> 01:26.462
<i>you won't let her stay
with you.</i>

01:26.545 --> 01:28.631
<i>She needs to hit rock bottom.</i>

01:38.933 --> 01:42.019
<i>♪♪ Think of all
the luck you got ♪♪</i>

01:42.103 --> 01:45.272
<i>♪♪ Know that
it's not for naught ♪♪</i>

01:45.356 --> 01:48.359
<i>♪♪ You were beaming
once before ♪♪</i>

01:48.442 --> 01:52.613
<i>♪♪ But it's not like that
anymore ♪♪</i>

01:52.696 --> 01:56.117
<i>♪♪ What is this downside ♪♪</i>

01:56.200 --> 01:59.495
<i>♪♪ That you speak of? ♪♪</i>

01:59.578 --> 02:01.580
<i>♪♪ What is this feeling ♪♪</i>

02:01.664 --> 02:06.293
<i>♪♪ You're so sure of? ♪♪</i>

02:13.050 --> 02:16.428
<i>♪♪ Round up
the friends you got ♪♪</i>

02:16.512 --> 02:19.515
<i>♪♪ Know that
they're not for naught ♪♪</i>

02:19.598 --> 02:22.768
<i>♪♪ You were willing
once before ♪♪</i>

02:22.852 --> 02:27.189
<i>♪♪ But it's not like that
anymore ♪♪</i>

02:27.273 --> 02:30.526
<i>♪♪ What is this downside ♪♪</i>

02:30.609 --> 02:34.029
<i>♪♪ That you speak of? ♪♪</i>

02:34.113 --> 02:35.906
<i>♪♪ What is this feeling ♪♪</i>

02:35.990 --> 02:39.869
<i>♪♪ You're so sure of? ♪♪</i>

03:15.070 --> 03:16.697
What the fuck were you doing

03:16.780 --> 03:17.781
in there?
You crazy?

03:17.865 --> 03:19.200
I was just--I just--calm--

03:19.283 --> 03:20.576
Get the hell out of here!

03:20.659 --> 03:21.619
You trying to get yourself
killed?

03:25.372 --> 03:26.707
Are you all right, man?

03:26.790 --> 03:27.583
Yeah.

03:27.666 --> 03:28.500
Are you sure?

03:28.584 --> 03:30.586
You went down hard.

03:30.669 --> 03:32.046
Joey, you better call
an ambulance.

03:32.129 --> 03:33.214
No, no.
No--

03:33.297 --> 03:34.965
No ambulance.
I'm fine.

03:38.552 --> 03:40.930
Are you sure, buddy?

03:41.013 --> 03:42.223
Yeah.

03:42.306 --> 03:43.933
I'm right as rain.

03:45.559 --> 03:47.186
Okay.

03:52.274 --> 03:53.484
I'm--

03:53.567 --> 03:54.860
I'm--I'm fine.

04:02.326 --> 04:03.994
I just bruised myself.

04:31.230 --> 04:32.815
Hey.
How was work?

04:32.898 --> 04:34.400
Long.
Franny asleep?

04:34.483 --> 04:36.735
<i>Yeah, I didn't hear
a peep all night.</i>

04:36.819 --> 04:38.362
She's up now.

04:46.537 --> 04:47.913
<i>Fuck off, Debbie.</i>

04:47.997 --> 04:49.456
Carl, it's Fiona.

04:51.583 --> 04:53.460
Come on, I gotta pee.

04:56.338 --> 04:58.132
Carl!

05:07.016 --> 05:08.350
What was that about?

05:08.434 --> 05:10.519
Kelly broke up with him.

05:18.902 --> 05:20.279
How much longer, babe?

05:20.362 --> 05:22.531
I think my calf
is starting to cramp.

05:22.614 --> 05:23.866
30 more seconds.

05:23.949 --> 05:24.992
30 seconds, and then

05:25.075 --> 05:26.327
we can make sweet, sweet love

05:26.410 --> 05:28.454
for hours and hours,
days, even.

05:28.537 --> 05:30.998
I am.
I am getting a cramp.

05:31.081 --> 05:32.207
Two weeks!

05:32.291 --> 05:33.292
Two weeks, baby,

05:33.375 --> 05:35.044
without your wonderfulness.

05:35.127 --> 05:36.503
Just a few more seconds.

05:36.587 --> 05:37.713
When the vasectomy doctor said

05:37.796 --> 05:38.881
you had to wait two weeks,

05:38.964 --> 05:40.507
I don't think
he literally meant

05:40.591 --> 05:42.343
- you had to wait for--
- Five, four--here we go.

05:42.426 --> 05:44.720
Two.
One.

05:47.806 --> 05:48.807
Oh...

05:48.891 --> 05:50.225
Okay.

05:50.309 --> 05:51.643
Take it a little easier.

05:51.727 --> 05:53.270
- Feels so good.
- Uh, I know,

05:53.354 --> 05:54.563
but we don't want

05:54.646 --> 05:55.647
to break the bed,

05:55.731 --> 05:57.066
or me.

05:57.149 --> 06:00.194
Oh.

06:07.409 --> 06:09.161
Kev?

06:12.331 --> 06:13.332
Did you just--

06:13.415 --> 06:15.125
Mm-hmm.

06:16.460 --> 06:18.212
Okay, then.

06:28.472 --> 06:30.140
Coffee?

06:30.224 --> 06:31.809
Almost.

06:39.024 --> 06:40.401
How you feeling?

06:44.530 --> 06:46.865
A little rough around the edges
in the morning.

06:46.949 --> 06:48.492
- You know?
- Sure.

06:54.373 --> 06:56.500
How's Xan?

06:56.583 --> 06:59.586
Uh, I might get to see her
in a couple days.

06:59.670 --> 07:02.714
Foster family signed off,
but I need DCFS approval.

07:04.174 --> 07:05.509
Wanna catch a meeting
this morning?

07:08.137 --> 07:09.805
Yeah, thanks.

07:15.811 --> 07:17.146
Here.

07:17.229 --> 07:18.147
Thanks.

07:18.230 --> 07:19.523
What happened to your face?

07:19.606 --> 07:20.524
Fryer at work.

07:20.607 --> 07:22.025
Don't pick.

07:22.109 --> 07:24.111
God, you'll make scars.

07:24.194 --> 07:27.406
Urlacher over Butkus?
No, not a chance.

07:27.489 --> 07:28.657
Butkus was an animal.

07:28.740 --> 07:29.867
Eight pro bowls.

07:29.950 --> 07:31.452
Hall of Fame.

07:31.535 --> 07:34.079
Have you checked out Butkus
on YouTube?

07:35.747 --> 07:37.749
Pre-concussion rules?

07:37.833 --> 07:39.626
He would've kicked
Khalil Mack's ass

07:39.710 --> 07:41.795
if they'd played together.
That's a fact.

07:41.879 --> 07:43.005
Okay.

07:43.088 --> 07:44.923
See you outside in five.

07:45.674 --> 07:46.717
Kelly.
We're going

07:46.800 --> 07:47.843
back-to-school shopping

07:47.926 --> 07:48.927
for guns and ammunition

07:49.011 --> 07:50.304
and things.

07:50.387 --> 07:51.430
Didn't you just get back home

07:51.513 --> 07:52.973
from working all night?

07:53.056 --> 07:54.933
Don't feel sleepy.
I'll catch it up later.

07:55.017 --> 07:57.060
Urlacher over Butkus.
Can you believe that shit?

07:57.144 --> 07:58.270
Uh, Franny?

07:58.353 --> 07:59.855
Taking her with.

08:02.399 --> 08:04.568
I gotta go.

08:07.613 --> 08:09.072
Lip Gallagher around?

08:09.156 --> 08:10.407
Uh, yeah, he's inside.

08:10.491 --> 08:11.492
Hey, watch your step.

08:11.575 --> 08:12.618
There's a homeless guy

08:12.701 --> 08:14.411
passed out on the sidewalk.

08:17.206 --> 08:19.041
He--a little help?

08:24.838 --> 08:26.256
Frank?

08:28.300 --> 08:29.426
I think I broke something.

08:29.510 --> 08:30.511
Something bad?

08:30.594 --> 08:31.386
Leg.

08:31.470 --> 08:32.638
Uh, you want to call 911?

08:32.721 --> 08:34.056
No.

08:34.139 --> 08:35.807
Help me inside.

08:39.019 --> 08:40.437
What's Frank doing out here?

08:40.521 --> 08:42.231
Uh, he says he broke
his leg or something.

08:42.314 --> 08:43.857
Won't let me call 911.

08:43.941 --> 08:45.234
Hey.

08:45.317 --> 08:46.568
Hey.

08:46.652 --> 08:47.945
Hi.

08:48.028 --> 08:50.239
Carl.

08:52.366 --> 08:54.701
Is that blood?

08:54.785 --> 08:57.037
It's just a scratch.

09:00.082 --> 09:01.667
That's bone.

09:05.546 --> 09:07.589
Help me inside.

09:12.636 --> 09:14.638
For fuck's sake.
Someone grab his arms.

09:14.721 --> 09:16.056
I'll grab his good leg.

09:16.139 --> 09:17.558
Come on.

09:17.641 --> 09:19.726
Easy, easy, easy.

09:19.810 --> 09:23.146
will you fucking--ow.

09:24.189 --> 09:25.107
Oh, God.

09:25.190 --> 09:27.734
Hello!

09:27.818 --> 09:29.361
Is Lip around?

09:29.444 --> 09:31.113
Uh, I think he might--

09:32.197 --> 09:33.156
Um...

09:33.240 --> 09:34.241
Uh, hi,

09:34.324 --> 09:35.826
Mr. Tamietti.

09:35.909 --> 09:37.578
You and I need to talk, son.

09:37.661 --> 09:39.162
Oh, yeah?

09:39.246 --> 09:40.372
Tami's having this baby,

09:40.455 --> 09:42.165
and I need to know
what your plan is.

09:43.500 --> 09:45.627
Uh, she's--she's keeping
the baby?

09:45.711 --> 09:46.962
I mean,
she seemed undecided

09:47.045 --> 09:48.463
- the last that we, uh--
- Oh, yeah.

09:48.547 --> 09:50.340
She's keeping the baby.
That's not open

09:50.424 --> 09:51.508
for discussion.

09:51.592 --> 09:53.510
No, no, sir.
I just mean, um,

09:53.594 --> 09:56.096
last time we talked,
she--she seemed unclear

09:56.179 --> 09:57.347
about what she wanted to do.

09:57.431 --> 09:58.807
Oh, it's clear.
She's having the baby.

09:58.890 --> 10:00.392
Good God.
Almost there.

10:00.475 --> 10:02.311
- A little help here!
- Okay, okay, okay.

10:02.394 --> 10:03.395
Put me down.
Put me down, no more.

10:03.478 --> 10:04.813
Down there! Down there!

10:04.896 --> 10:06.315
Jesus.

10:06.398 --> 10:07.357
What happened?

10:07.441 --> 10:08.191
He busted his leg.

10:08.275 --> 10:09.526
Is that bone?

10:09.610 --> 10:10.986
What the fuck?
Why didn't you

10:11.069 --> 10:12.070
call an ambulance?

10:12.154 --> 10:13.030
He wouldn't let us.

10:13.113 --> 10:14.072
The hell is that?

10:14.156 --> 10:15.657
Mollies...

10:15.741 --> 10:17.534
- A few personal items.
- ...And acid.

10:17.618 --> 10:18.493
Is that why
you didn't want

10:18.577 --> 10:19.453
to call an ambulance?

10:19.536 --> 10:20.746
Uh, who the hell is that?

10:20.829 --> 10:21.955
Our dad.

10:22.039 --> 10:23.123
Why doesn't he want
an ambulance?

10:23.206 --> 10:24.249
Because the paramedics

10:24.333 --> 10:25.667
would've emptied his pockets,

10:25.751 --> 10:27.294
found the drugs,
and called the cops.

10:27.377 --> 10:28.545
Uh, you know, Mr. Tamietti,
why don't we go get

10:28.629 --> 10:29.838
a cup of coffee
or something, yeah?

10:29.921 --> 10:31.548
I had an opportunity
to invest

10:31.632 --> 10:34.176
some of my Ingrid
severance money, and I took it.

10:34.259 --> 10:35.260
If you're done hiding
your stash,

10:35.344 --> 10:36.928
can I call 911?

10:37.012 --> 10:38.430
Not until my associates come

10:38.513 --> 10:40.849
and we complete
our transaction.

10:40.932 --> 10:42.017
I gotta go to work.

10:43.518 --> 10:44.728
Yeah, we should go, too.

10:44.811 --> 10:45.937
I'll give
your associates

10:46.021 --> 10:47.189
five minutes.

10:47.272 --> 10:48.440
Then I'm calling 911.

10:48.523 --> 10:50.942
Borrow your phone?

10:54.529 --> 10:56.615
- Mail.
- Ah, I'm late for--

10:56.698 --> 10:58.116
work.

11:07.626 --> 11:08.627
Ah, crap.

11:08.710 --> 11:09.753
I forgot the stroller.

11:09.836 --> 11:11.296
Take her.

11:51.294 --> 11:53.130
Excuse me.

11:53.213 --> 11:54.423
Excuse me.

11:54.506 --> 11:55.882
Move.

12:14.276 --> 12:15.277
Frank again?

12:17.070 --> 12:18.447
Yeah.

12:38.425 --> 12:39.676
Open femur fracture.

12:39.760 --> 12:41.470
Definitely going
to need surgery.

12:41.553 --> 12:45.223
I'm in a lot of pain here.
Could I get 15 of morphine?

12:45.307 --> 12:48.101
No can do, Frank.

12:48.185 --> 12:49.186
Lidoc--

12:49.269 --> 12:50.395
is that lidocaine?

12:50.479 --> 12:51.563
Yep.

12:51.646 --> 12:53.732
Ah, come on, guys!

12:53.815 --> 12:55.776
You got any fentanyl in there?

12:55.859 --> 12:57.319
That'd take the edge off.

12:57.402 --> 12:58.612
Can give you
a bite block

12:58.695 --> 13:01.031
to chomp down on
if you like.

13:01.114 --> 13:02.365
A bite block?

13:02.449 --> 13:04.326
What are you,
the Marquis de Sade?

13:04.409 --> 13:06.536
Best I can do after last time.

13:06.620 --> 13:10.165
I did not steal drugs
from your ambulance.

13:10.248 --> 13:12.083
I saw you take it, Frank.

13:12.167 --> 13:13.877
Are you sure you don't want
that bite block?

13:13.960 --> 13:16.338
This might sting.

13:16.421 --> 13:18.423
Fuck you, Quincy.

13:26.139 --> 13:27.682
Personally, I would've taken
the bite block.

13:29.267 --> 13:31.144
You want to ride
with him again?

13:31.228 --> 13:32.896
How long's the wait
at County this morning?

13:32.979 --> 13:35.106
Pro hockey season's shorter.

13:35.190 --> 13:36.775
- Ow! Ow! Ow! Ouch!
- Okay.

13:36.858 --> 13:39.110
Let me get my purse and tell
my brother we're leaving.

13:39.194 --> 13:40.529
Easy, easy, easy, e--

13:40.612 --> 13:41.613
Keep whining, Frank,

13:41.696 --> 13:42.823
and I'll find every pothole

13:42.906 --> 13:43.907
between here and County

13:43.990 --> 13:45.283
to bounce you over.

13:45.367 --> 13:46.827
Hey, Liam?

13:46.910 --> 13:49.246
I gotta take Frank
to the ER,

13:49.329 --> 13:52.415
so you have to make
yourself breakfast, okay?

13:52.499 --> 13:54.042
Hey.

14:02.259 --> 14:03.677
Liam?

14:11.810 --> 14:14.187
You want Tabasco?

14:14.271 --> 14:15.939
Eight seconds.

14:18.692 --> 14:21.278
It's only been two weeks
since the surgery, babe.

14:21.361 --> 14:22.821
Give it some time.

14:26.116 --> 14:28.076
12-year-olds
last longer.

14:28.869 --> 14:31.413
All right, girls, finish up.
It's almost time for school.

14:31.496 --> 14:34.791
Is this what it's gonna be like
from now on?

14:34.875 --> 14:36.042
Eight seconds?

14:36.126 --> 14:37.460
You really think
we need to be having

14:37.544 --> 14:38.962
this conversation
in front of the girls?

14:39.045 --> 14:41.548
Wham, bam, thank you, ma'am.
That's me now.

14:41.631 --> 14:44.509
Mr. Kevin Ball,
the "wham, bam" man.

14:44.593 --> 14:46.469
Okay, girls.
Dishes in the sink

14:46.553 --> 14:48.305
and backpacks.
Let's go.

14:52.893 --> 14:55.061
I'm so sorry I let them
cut you guys.

14:55.145 --> 14:56.479
Can you ever forgive me?

14:56.563 --> 14:58.398
You're gonna live, baby.

14:58.481 --> 15:00.734
It's one tiny incision.

15:08.450 --> 15:10.535
<i>Wait for Mommy.</i>

15:12.078 --> 15:14.080
Oh, God.

15:17.292 --> 15:19.419
Your sister coming again
this morning?

15:19.502 --> 15:21.463
She said she was, yeah.

15:23.965 --> 15:26.468
Tami's dad showed up
at my house this morning.

15:26.551 --> 15:28.261
- Bob?
- Yeah.

15:28.345 --> 15:29.888
Shit.
What did he want?

15:29.971 --> 15:32.057
Wants to know my plan.

15:32.140 --> 15:33.141
You have a plan?

15:33.224 --> 15:34.434
No.

15:34.517 --> 15:35.727
Tami's made it very clear

15:35.810 --> 15:37.771
that I'm not allowed
to have one.

15:37.854 --> 15:39.814
Don't fuck with Bob.

15:39.898 --> 15:41.441
He's tougher than he looks.

15:41.524 --> 15:43.902
He said Tami's
definitely having the baby.

15:45.028 --> 15:46.529
That's the Tamiettis.

15:46.613 --> 15:48.740
Old-school Catholics.

15:48.823 --> 15:51.785
Big families
and fish on Fridays.

15:51.868 --> 15:54.245
She tell you she was going
to see a doctor today?

15:55.413 --> 15:56.581
No.

15:56.665 --> 15:58.917
This afternoon.

15:59.000 --> 16:02.170
Asked Cami to go,
but she's working until 6:00.

16:02.253 --> 16:04.422
W-what kind of doctor?
Did she say?

16:04.506 --> 16:05.882
Nope.

16:06.508 --> 16:08.843
Tami likes to stick it
to her dad.

16:08.927 --> 16:11.721
Could be she's getting ready
to solve your problem.

16:13.848 --> 16:15.183
It's starting.

16:15.266 --> 16:16.267
Yeah.

16:36.496 --> 16:37.497
All right.
Coke,

16:37.580 --> 16:39.249
crackers, and a bedpan.

16:39.332 --> 16:41.668
Barb's saying three hours,
but could be five.

16:41.751 --> 16:43.211
I can't stay the whole time.
I got a meeting.

16:43.294 --> 16:45.839
Oh, Christ.
AA?

16:45.922 --> 16:49.384
Did you let Lip recruit you
into that cult?

16:49.467 --> 16:51.469
Meeting with a public defender.

16:51.553 --> 16:53.722
Trouble with the law?
Excuse me.

16:53.805 --> 16:55.598
I've got a bone
sticking out of my thigh.

16:55.682 --> 16:58.560
Does this look
like a scam to you?

16:58.643 --> 17:00.103
Hey, doc.

17:00.186 --> 17:02.355
Could you hook a brother up
with a little morphine

17:02.439 --> 17:03.940
for a broken femur?

17:04.024 --> 17:05.900
Come on, I--

17:05.984 --> 17:08.862
Ah, that's right.
Just walk on by, Osama.

17:08.945 --> 17:10.739
We'll have your ass
